. Error bars shows the 95% confidence interval. Comparing the evolution of the DJF CMIP zonal (middle row) and North Pacific (bottom row) mean, averaged between 40°−60°, vertically integrated eddy momentum flux convergence (\(-\frac{\partial \overline{{u}^{{\prime} }{v}^{{\prime} }}}{\partial y}\)) and EKE and \(-\frac{\partial {\rm{SLP}}}{\partial y}\). Shadings show the  ± 2 s.d. across the models.Extended Data Fig. 6 Sensitivity tests for ΔySLPy.The 1979-2014 trends in \(\phi {{\rm{EKE}}}_{\max }\) plotted against the 1979–2014 trends in ΔySLPy, estimated as the difference between a, 45°−65° N and 25°−45° N, b, 40°−70° N and 10−40° N, and c, 40°−65° N and 15°−40° N, across CMIP6 (blue dots) and CMIP5 (blue squares) models; their correlation appears in the upper left corners. Blue lines and shadings show the linear regressions ±2 s.d. (Methods). The mean and the 5%−95% range of the 1979−2014 trends in the observed ΔySLPy (green), CMIP \(\phi {{\rm{EKE}}}_{\max }\) (black), reanalyses \(\phi {{\rm{EKE}}}_{\max }\) (red) and the constrained \(\phi {{\rm{EKE}}}_{\max }\) (purple).Extended Data Fig. 7 Extending the emergent constraint analysis.a, The evolution, relative to the 1979–1988 period, of \(\phi {{\rm{EKE}}}_{\max }\) (black line) and ΔySLPy (blue line) in CMIP mean; their correlation is in the upper-left corner. Shadings show the ± 2 s.d. across the models. The green line shows the evolution of ΔySLPy in observations over the 1979−2024 period using the preliminary ICOADS data. b, The 1979−2024 trends in \(\phi {{\rm{EKE}}}_{\max }\) plotted against the 1979–2024 trends in ΔySLPy across CMIP6 (blue dots) and CMIP5 (blue squares) models; their correlation appears in the upper left corner. Blue line and shading show the linear regression ± 2 s.d. (Methods). The mean and the 5%−95% range of the 1979−2024 trends in the observed ΔySLPy (green), CMIP \(\phi {{\rm{EKE}}}_{\max }\) (black), reanalyses \(\phi {{\rm{EKE}}}_{\max }\) (red) and the constrained \(\phi {{\